The paper proposes a novel statistical approach for predicting landslides using deep convolutional networks. The approach involves using a standardized dataset of georeferenced images consisting of slope, elevation, land cover, lithology, rock age, and rock family as inputs to deliver a landslide susceptibility map as output. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves using images as inputs. Additionally, the use of deep convolutional networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves geospatial analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of statistical methods and the development of a novel model suggest that the paper may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
